content.description: Stand start move up on slopey holds till you reach the positive horizontal crack (beware of the loose death block wedged in the crack).  top out up and to the right.  As this cleans up it may get better but mossy for now
content.location: about 15 feet to the left of off route

content.description: Same start as Cool 2, but continue right into small gully.  Then find your way up using good holds.
content.protection: pads... please protect punji pit from possible piercing and potential painful penetrating puncturing power.
content.location: continues to the right of Cool 2

content.description: SDS on decent holds low and to the left off the start holds for off route.  Make a big right hand move to the start of off route and continue from there
content.protection: on front face of the Next Block while walking from the Whatever Wall

content.description: This takes the obviouse line up the front side of the boulder as you walk at it from the Whatever Wall.  Start on crimps at eye level then move up to awesome vertical crack that continues to top.
content.location: on front face of the Next Block while walking from the Whatever Wall

content.description: Stand start on crimps and climbs straight up on, suprise, more crimps plus a horizontal crack
content.location: couple feet to the left of off route

content.description: Start on same holds as "Cool 1" but move out right to a good hold.   Hit the gaston and rock up to the nice rail above.  Use slopers straight up to mantle out.   A more difficult sit start would go for this one.
Stand start with hands on obvious start hold mixture at chest level.   Move out left to cool vertical crimp then use sloping crimp and the sloping arete to the the top.
content.protection: a pad/ a filler pad for weird landing
content.location: Once you past the boulders coming from the the ultimate area, the climbs are around to the left.

content.description: This is the next nice boulder you get to while continuing on the trail from the whatever wall "which is now cleaned" the trail cuts directly next to this bloc, forcing you to squeeze between the boulder and another fallen piece to the right of trail.   These are slaby-er climbs but are a lot of fun.  Still some potential that could be cleaned.
